  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240&deg;C/ 220&deg;C (fan)/ 475&deg;F/ Gas 9</p>\r\n<p>Add half&nbsp;of the<strong> smoked streaky</strong>&nbsp;<strong>bacon</strong>&nbsp;(you'll use the rest later) to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the <strong>bacon</strong> is very crispy</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the<strong>&nbsp;crispy bacon</strong>&nbsp;to kitchen paper (you'll use this for garnishing at the end) and keep the baking tray for later!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and cut them into bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain the <strong>potatoes</strong> and return them to the pot, leaving them to steam-dry</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the remaining<strong> bacon</strong> into small bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>Cumberland</strong><strong> sausages</strong> to the reserved baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until they're golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>bacon&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 3 min or until crispy</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>crispy bacon</strong> to&nbsp;kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to low and add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10 min or until it's softened&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/942.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
